    <b><font size="+3">Life Cycle and Process Models in Software Engineering</font></b>
<ul>
  <li>This presentation is associated with the article, <a
 href="http://www.ics.uci.edu/%7Ewscacchi/Papers/SE-Encyc/Process-Models-SE-Encyc.pdf">Process
Models in Software Engineering</a>. This article provides a survey   of tools,
techniques, and concepts for alternative software process models   and modeling
capabilities, and how they can be employed to support large team-oriented
 software development projects. Appears in J. Marciniak (ed.),        <i>Encyclopedia
of Software Engineering, 2nd. Edition</i>, 993-1005,  Wiley, 2002.</li>
</ul>
      
